  "text": "Planning pick-and-place motions can also be considered in a framework of task and motion planning [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] . A planning problem is solved through two layers of planning : high-level task planning and low-level motion planning. A task planner executes symbolic searches for high-level actions such as pick, move, and place, not considering geometries nor kinematics. A motion planner then computes actual commands to follow the strategy-a sequence of actions-given by the task planner.",
